JOHANNESBURG - The author of a fake MiWay email that circulated on social media last week has apologised for creating it. Mondli Madlala was identified as the email's author after an independent forensic investigation. The email seemed to show a MiWay employee referring to black people as baboons. READ: MiWay: audit proves racist mail is fake The insurance company denied the email was real and an investigation confirmed it had been created by Madlala, who was angry over a rejected insurance claim. Madlala agreed to a joint statement with the insurance company and has agreed to do talks at six schools about the dangers of social media. In return, MiWay will not be pressing charges against him. eNCA